âœ… Following Steps to upload the project into github : 
==========================================================

1ï¸âƒ£ Initialized Git 
git init   : : git init initializes an empty Git repository by creating the .git metadata directory.

âœ” Repository created correctly

2ï¸âƒ£ Staged all files
git add .   : All files moved from working directory â†’ staging area

Note: After `git add .` , you will show CRLF / LF Warnings
Meaning:
  1.You are on Windows
  2.Git is warning about line-ending conversion

| OS          | Line Ending |
| ----------- | ----------- |
| Windows     | CRLF        |
| Linux/macOS | LF          |


âœ” All project files added
âš  LF â†’ CRLF warnings â†’ harmless on Windows

3ï¸âƒ£ Verified staging
git status


âœ” Files correctly staged
âœ” No mistakes

4ï¸âƒ£ First commit
git commit -m "first commit"

Q: What happened internally?
--> Git created:
            1. A commit object
            2. A tree object
            3. Multiple blob objects

--> The commit now has:
            1. Commit ID: aee1af7
            2. Author
            3. Timestamp
            4. Snapshot of all staged files
âœ” Clean root commit
âœ” 15 files committed

5ï¸âƒ£ Set main branch
git branch -M main

Q: What happened?
--> Branch renamed to main
--> -M = force rename

Q: Why this matters:
--> GitHub uses main as default branch


6ï¸âƒ£ Connected to GitHub
git remote add origin https://github.com/Sahniajaykumar/card-components.git

Q: What happened?
--> Git stored a remote reference
--> Name: origin
--> URL: GitHub repository

âœ” Remote added correctly

7ï¸âƒ£ Pushed to GitHub
git push -u origin main


Q: What happened?
--> Git packaged commits
--> Sent them to GitHub
--> Created branch main on remote
--> Uploaded all files

ðŸ“Œ -u means: 
--> Set upstream
--> Future git push works without arguments

âœ” Push successful
âœ” Tracking set up
âœ” Repo is live ðŸš€
