Q: update project code to github first perform pull remote  
Step 1: Pull remote changes
Run: git pull origin main --allow-unrelated-histories
Explanation:
--> --allow-unrelated-histories â†’ because your local repo and remote repo have different starting commits
--> Git will merge the remote README (or any remote files) with your local project

Step 2: Resolve any merge conflicts
  1. git add .
  2. git commit -m "Merged remote changes"
  3. git push -u origin main


